didn't scar her at all.</i>

14:43.090 --> 14:45.009
- How about your brother?
How's he doing?

14:45.009 --> 14:46.969
- Uh, you know, works a lot.

14:46.969 --> 14:49.471
Anya, too.
But they seem happy.

14:49.471 --> 14:51.807
<i>According to Facebook.</i>

14:51.807 --> 14:53.642
- And how's school going?

14:53.642 --> 14:55.936
- It's great, actually. I'm--

14:55.936 --> 14:58.187
I'm just working on
building my portfolio.

14:58.187 --> 15:00.274
It's--it's more than just
that first book.

15:00.274 --> 15:02.192
[phone buzzing]
You really need the second

15:02.192 --> 15:04.110
if you're going--
- Hey, where are you guys?

15:04.110 --> 15:05.321
- [sighs]

15:05.321 --> 15:07.197
<i>Beck, you're such an asshole.</i>

15:07.197 --> 15:09.658
<i>"Love me, Daddy.
I'm gonna be a writer, Daddy."</i>

15:09.658 --> 15:11.951
<i>God, just shut up forever.</i>

15:11.951 --> 15:14.038
- There they are.

15:14.038 --> 15:16.081
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

15:16.081 --> 15:18.000
<i>- Oh, my God.</i>

15:18.000 --> 15:19.960
<i>She's actually gotten
more smug.</i>

15:19.960 --> 15:21.544
- Beck, look,
I have a cane.

15:21.544 --> 15:23.297
- Yes, you do.

15:23.297 --> 15:25.923
Look at you guys.

15:25.923 --> 15:27.884
- You look...pretty.

15:27.884 --> 15:29.345
<i>- Stop hating them.</i>

15:29.345 --> 15:30.596
<i>They're just kids.</i>

15:30.596 --> 15:31.679
<i>None of it's their fault.</i>

15:31.679 --> 15:34.099
Aw, thanks, Mia.
So do you.

15:34.099 --> 15:38.144
- Guinevere, how are you?

15:38.144 --> 15:40.522
Mm.
- Great. I love your dress.

15:40.522 --> 15:42.774
<i>- Not necessarily
you in it, but--</i>

15:42.774 --> 15:44.192
- I bought you something.

15:44.192 --> 15:45.485
Just couldn't resist.

15:45.485 --> 15:48.822
<i>- No, she's not.
</i>- Ohh. [gasps]

15:48.822 --> 15:51.240
Oh, it's perfect.

15:51.240 --> 15:53.701
Oh, um-- [clears throat]

15:53.701 --> 15:55.663
[whispering]
You're slipping a bit, dear.

15:55.663 --> 15:58.831
<i>- Touch me again, crazy pants.
I dare you.</i>

15:58.831 --> 16:00.292
Thank you.

16:00.292 --> 16:02.086
<i>[tense music]</i>

16:02.086 --> 16:04.837
- Play a game?

16:06.215 --> 16:08.258
<i>- You really are capable
of keeping a secret.</i>

16:08.258 --> 16:10.302
<i>Four, by my count.</i>

16:11.678 --> 16:13.846
<i>Who the hell are you, Beck?</i>

16:18.018 --> 16:20.979
[laughter]
- Hi, there.

16:20.979 --> 16:22.855
Hey! That's a boy.
- Oh! First try.

16:22.855 --> 16:24.232
- You're a natural.

16:24.232 --> 16:25.609
[clattering]
- Yo!

16:25.609 --> 16:28.861
- Two down.

16:28.861 --> 16:30.572
- What an arm on him.

16:30.572 --> 16:33.408
I know. I--I know I'm
embarrassing, I know.

16:33.408 --> 16:35.744
Babe, just get a shot
for the blog.

16:35.744 --> 16:37.870
- Ooh!
- [screams]

16:37.870 --> 16:39.748
<i>- If I wasn't so
blinded by love,</i>

16:39.748 --> 16:41.457
<i>I would've seen the secrets</i>

16:41.457 --> 16:43.751
<i>right in front of me,
waiting to be uncovered.</i>

16:43.751 --> 16:46.379
<i>Captain Beck.
AKA, The Captain.</i>

16:46.379 --> 16:50.759
<i>AKA, Edward Martin Beck.</i>

16:50.759 --> 16:52.260
<i>The addict part was true,
I see.</i>

16:52.260 --> 16:53.886
<i>But he never died,
which he credits</i>

16:53.886 --> 16:55.596
<i>to his friends in
the NA fellowship</i>

16:55.596 --> 16:58.225
<i>out of St. James Church.</i>

16:58.225 --> 17:00.309
<i>It was there that he
not only conquered his demons</i>

17:00.309 --> 17:02.229
<i>but also met church rep
and divorcée,</i>

17:02.229 --> 17:04.147
<i>Nancy Whitesell.</i>

17:04.147 --> 17:08.568
<i>AKA, "The Christian News'"
Mommy Blogger of the Year.</i>

17:08.568 --> 17:10.903
<i>"If Ned can do it,
so can you."</i>

17:10.903 --> 17:12.196
<i>He became a feature
in her blog.</i>

17:12.196 --> 17:14.115
<i>Then, her life.</i>

17:14.115 --> 17:17.452
<i>Less than a year,
they were married.</i>

17:17.452 --> 17:19.747
<i>He really landed himself
the perfect family.</i>

17:19.747 --> 17:22.415
<i>If your step-mother
is to be believed.</i>

17:22.415 --> 17:24.375
<i>But what about you, Beck.</i>

17:24.375 --> 17:26.878
<i>Where do you fit
into all this?</i>

17:26.878 --> 17:30.758
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:31.759 --> 17:35.596
[brass band music]

17:35.596 --> 17:37.513
- [sighs]

17:43.269 --> 17:46.565
Your father has come
such a long way.

17:46.565 --> 17:48.317
He worked hard for it, too.

17:48.317 --> 17:49.777
<i>- You're barking up
the wrong tree, lady,</i>

17:49.777 --> 17:50.861
<i>if you think
I'm gonna sit here</i>

17:50.861 --> 17:52.153
<i>and validate that man.</i>

17:52.153 --> 17:54.948
Yeah, he's, uh--
he's lucky to have you.

17:54.948 --> 17:56.741
- Hm.

17:56.741 --> 17:58.701
Just goes to show you
what a good Christian household

17:58.701 --> 18:00.621
and loving family can do.

18:00.621 --> 18:02.705
<i>- She did not just suggest
if you were more Christian</i>

18:02.705 --> 18:05.083
<i>he wouldn't have abandoned you
for a crack pipe.</i>

18:05.917 --> 18:08.377
- Mommy, come watch me.

18:08.377 --> 18:11.464
- Excuse me, my dear.

18:14.050 --> 18:16.095
- [sighs]

18:18.596 --> 18:20.140
- [sighs]

18:20.140 --> 18:22.017
Your dad talk to you yet?

18:22.017 --> 18:25.061
<i>- She's so her mother,
only less subtle.</i>

18:25.061 --> 18:27.815
Talk to me about--
- Well, he's supposed to

18:27.815 --> 18:31.527
tell you he can't
send money anymore.

18:31.527 --> 18:33.820
But he's gonna help you
find a better job first.

18:33.820 --> 18:36.531
[sighs] Mom doesn't think
he should wait.

18:36.531 --> 18:38.659
She's so cranky.

18:38.659 --> 18:41.953
It's the hormones.

18:41.953 --> 18:45.289
Oh. I wasn't supposed
to tell you,

18:45.289 --> 18:48.501
but she's pregnant.

18:48.501 --> 18:49.920
That's why they're
fighting about it.

18:49.920 --> 18:51.838
<i>- Great. That's great.</i>

18:51.838 --> 18:54.799
<i>He's starting a new family.</i>

18:54.799 --> 18:59.512
<i>Because fixing the one he had
obviously wasn't an option.</i>

18:59.512 --> 19:03.182
<i>Why would he ever do that?</i>

19:05.352 --> 19:07.688
I'm going to find a bathroom.
I'll be right back.

19:07.688 --> 19:14.694
♪ ♪

19:16.028 --> 19:19.365
Can I get another
Timber Doodle?

19:31.169 --> 19:32.837
Uh! Bitch.

19:32.837 --> 19:35.840
<i>[rock music]</i>

19:35.840 --> 19:42.847
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:45.308 --> 19:48.394
- Hi. Is Joe Goldberg
working today?

19:48.394 --> 19:50.730
- Joe Goldberg is not
working today.

19:50.730 --> 19:52.900
But, uh, I'm Ethan.

19:52.900 --> 19:55.067
And you would be--
- Looking for Joe.

19:55.067 --> 19:57.653
Expect him anytime soon?
- I do not.

19:57.653 --> 20:00.073
Uh, relatively speaking.
Joe's out of town.

20:00.073 --> 20:01.909
But is there anything
I can help you find?

20:01.909 --> 20:04.076
- Possibly.
I'm in the market

20:04.076 --> 20:06.579
for a first-edition copy
of "Ozma of Oz."

20:06.579 --> 20:08.832
- Oh, that's a pretty rare
critter.

20:08.832 --> 20:10.334
Uh, not sure we have it.

20:10.334 --> 20:11.792
See, books of
that pedigree we keep

20:11.792 --> 20:14.046
under lock and key
downstairs.

20:14.046 --> 20:16.632
- And you don't have the key?

20:16.632 --> 20:18.717
- Well, normally
I have the key.

20:18.717 --> 20:20.509
But I just don't
have it right now.

20:20.509 --> 20:22.930
Uh, Joe left with it. He just
forgot to give it to me.

20:22.930 --> 20:25.807
- And where is Joe?

20:25.807 --> 20:28.559
[cell phone ringing]

20:28.559 --> 20:30.604
- I thought I was supposed
to be writing.

20:30.604 --> 20:32.271
- Are you with Eight Seconds?

20:32.271 --> 20:34.441
- No, I told you.
I'm on a retreat.

20:34.441 --> 20:35.817
- Is he with you?

20:35.817 --> 20:38.111
[cell phone buzzes]

20:38.111 --> 20:39.820
- What is it, Ethan?
<i> - Hey, bro.</i>

20:39.820 --> 20:41.865
Uh, I know you didn't
wanna be interrupted,

20:41.865 --> 20:43.784
but, uh, this chick
was just in asking about

20:43.784 --> 20:46.662
<i>a first ed. "Ozma of Oz."
</i>- What are you talking about?

20:46.662 --> 20:48.788
- Joe's there, in Nyack.

20:48.788 --> 20:51.959
- What did she look like?
- Uh, 25-ish, brunette,

20:51.959 --> 20:54.795
kinda hot, but you know,
maybe that's like a type thing.

20:54.795 --> 20:56.462
<i>- Peach Salinger.</i>

20:56.462 --> 20:58.214
- Are you lying to me?
<i> - Of course you are,</i>

20:58.214 --> 20:59.633
<i>that's what you do,</i>

20:59.633 --> 21:00.759
<i>lie so your life
looks better.</i>

21:00.759 --> 21:03.095
Peach, I'm--I'm not lying.

21:03.095 --> 21:05.305
I told you,
I'm here to write. I--

21:05.305 --> 21:06.973
I can't deal
with this right now

21:06.973 --> 21:09.643
I promise I'll call you.
- And you told her I'm here?

21:09.643 --> 21:12.061
<i>- I'm sorry, man.
Did I screw up or--</i>

21:12.061 --> 21:14.480
<i>- You'll know I'm here.
You may already know.</i>

21:14.480 --> 21:17.275
- Hey, you. Oh, sorry.

21:17.275 --> 21:18.442
So sorry.

21:18.442 --> 21:20.487
<i>- How is this explainable?</i>

21:20.487 --> 21:23.240
<i>Do I run?
Shit, shit, shit.</i>

21:23.240 --> 21:26.201
<i>[light music]</i>

21:26.201 --> 21:33.250
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:35.751 --> 21:37.837
- Joe?

21:37.837 --> 21:39.381
- Beck?

21:39.381 --> 21:40.757
What are you doing here?

21:48.432 --> 21:50.892
[fiddle music]

21:50.892 --> 21:54.270
- That's true, you are
a book seller, aren't you?

21:54.270 --> 21:57.898
- Sadly, I humiliate myself
like this annually.

21:57.898 --> 22:01.318
- Mm. Well, this is kinda
working for ya.

22:01.318 --> 22:02.695
- You mock.
- [laughs]

22:02.695 --> 22:05.323
- It's--it's fair.

22:05.323 --> 22:07.325
[sighs]

22:08.868 --> 22:11.371
I'm--I'm lying.
I'm lying to you right now.

22:11.371 --> 22:13.832
- Excuse me?
- I knew you were here.

22:13.832 --> 22:16.167
I wasn't happy with how
we left things.

22:16.167 --> 22:17.294
And apparently,
neither were you,

22:17.294 --> 22:18.670
seeing as how you were

22:18.670 --> 22:20.255
hiding out in the bathroom.
- I--I--

22:20.255 --> 22:22.089
I wasn't hiding, I swear.

22:22.089 --> 22:24.468
- We can at least agree
that I may

22:24.468 --> 22:26.595
have left you a little wanting.

22:26.595 --> 22:28.512
- Yeah--
- So, you're saying you did

22:28.512 --> 22:30.057
want it to last
longer than eight seconds?

22:30.057 --> 22:32.349
- No! I mean--yeah.
As in--

22:32.349 --> 22:34.144
- Wait, I thought
it was a race.

22:34.144 --> 22:35.895
Didn't I win?

22:35.895 --> 22:38.105
No. Um--

22:38.105 --> 22:41.151
I just--I thought it'd be nice
if I came and surprised you.

22:41.151 --> 22:43.653
And not leave you with...

22:43.653 --> 22:46.573
that memory of me for too long.

22:48.115 --> 22:50.660
- How did you, um--

22:50.660 --> 22:52.369
How did you know I was here?

22:52.369 --> 22:55.164
- Oh, well, you posted
a nature shot this morning.

22:55.164 --> 22:57.917
See that little restaurant sign
in the background?

22:57.917 --> 23:00.586
Apparently, Pops and Millie's
ain't a chain.

23:00.586 --> 23:02.463
- Mm, shocking.
Really should be.

23:02.463 --> 23:04.132
- Yeah.

23:04.132 --> 23:05.842
So I Googled it
and I saw all the information

23:05.842 --> 23:07.426
about the festival
and I figured

23:07.426 --> 23:08.804
this was probably why
you were in the area.

23:08.804 --> 23:09.930
And by the way,
this outfit

23:09.930 --> 23:11.222
is really working on you, too.

23:11.222 --> 23:13.016
- Ohh.

23:13.016 --> 23:15.227
Um--

23:15.227 --> 23:16.603
[sighs]

23:16.603 --> 23:19.772
Can you hold on
for just one second?

23:21.273 --> 23:23.734
- Hey, sweetie.
Cooper's kinda hitting a wall.

23:23.734 --> 23:25.612
We were gonna head back
and rest up before dinner.

23:25.612 --> 23:27.114
- Oh, okay. I'll find my own

23:27.114 --> 23:29.115
ride back to the hotel, so--

23:29.115 --> 23:31.701
- And who is this
handsome gentleman?

23:31.701 --> 23:34.578
- Sorry, this is--
this is Joe.

23:34.578 --> 23:37.124
He works at a book store
I go to in the city.

23:37.124 --> 23:39.334
- Well, hey, Joe.

23:39.334 --> 23:41.670
- This is my wife, Nancy.
I'm--I'm Ned, Beck's dad.

23:41.670 --> 23:44.213
- Hi.
- Hey, nice to meet you both.

23:44.213 --> 23:46.799
- You're welcome to join us
for dinner, Joe.

23:46.799 --> 23:49.845
- Yes! Totally.
If you can.

23:49.845 --> 23:52.471
[sighs]
- I--I'd love to.

23:52.471 --> 23:55.142
- We'll see you then.

23:56.726 --> 23:58.478
- Okay, uh--

23:58.478 --> 23:59.729
I can explain.

23:59.729 --> 24:02.648
Um--

24:02.648 --> 24:03.692
[sighs]

24:03.692 --> 24:06.236
One day, when I was, um, 12,

24:06.236 --> 24:09.489
I got home from school
before my brother and sister.

24:09.489 --> 24:11.615
My mom was at work.

24:11.615 --> 24:15.537
So I go into the basement
to play "Mario Brothers"

24:15.537 --> 24:19.207
And I, uh--I find...

24:19.207 --> 24:21.667
my father...

24:21.667 --> 24:25.462
unconscious, with a needle
in his arm.

24:27.590 --> 24:30.426
I thought he was dead.

24:30.426 --> 24:32.345
- I'm so sorry

24:32.345 --> 24:33.680
you had to go through that.

24:33.680 --> 24:36.348
- I mean, he survived it.

24:36.348 --> 24:40.686
And--which, of course,
was this amazing thing.

24:40.686 --> 24:43.690
So when he disappeared on us
because he relapsed,

24:43.690 --> 24:45.442
I just--

24:45.442 --> 24:47.986
I couldn't believe it.

24:47.986 --> 24:53.532
Right then and there,
I decided he was dead.

24:53.532 --> 24:56.076
Which is why I told you he was,
which is...

24:56.076 --> 24:57.746
[sighs]

24:57.746 --> 25:00.957
totally wrong, I mean,
who does that?

25:00.957 --> 25:04.336
[chuckles] The first deep,
personal thing

25:04.336 --> 25:06.128
I tell you is a total lie.

25:06.128 --> 25:08.589
- Well, hang on. That's--

25:08.589 --> 25:10.759
- No, I get it if you
are horrified

25:10.759 --> 25:12.384
and think I'm a total fraud
and liar

25:12.384 --> 25:14.596
and want nothing to do with me.

25:14.596 --> 25:17.348
- After everything
you've been through?

25:17.348 --> 25:18.682
I get it.

25:18.682 --> 25:20.977
I'm sorry.

25:22.645 --> 25:24.021
- [chuckles]

25:24.021 --> 25:26.191
You're sorry?

25:28.234 --> 25:30.237
- I am.

25:32.197 --> 25:34.990
- Anyway, I was--
I was at Brown

25:34.990 --> 25:37.576
and he tracked me down
to say he had gotten clean.

25:37.576 --> 25:39.788
And then he says
he wants to help

25:39.788 --> 25:43.290
with my school
and some of my bills.

25:43.290 --> 25:47.753
Like dad amends.
So I bury my resentment

25:47.753 --> 25:49.838
and start having
lunches with him

25:49.838 --> 25:52.925
and doing stupid
shit like this.

25:52.925 --> 25:55.511
Playing the dutiful daughter.

25:55.511 --> 25:59.348
Enduring this nauseatingly
perfect new family of his.

25:59.348 --> 26:02.143
- I'm sure they're not perfect.
- Believe me,

26:02.143 --> 26:04.270
they are.
- Well, I guess

26:04.270 --> 26:06.690
I'll find out tonight.
- No. [laughs]

26:06.690 --> 26:08.232
I'm not subjecting you to that.

26:08.232 --> 26:11.068
I'll just--I'll tell them
you had to go back.

26:11.068 --> 26:13.320
Book emergency.
- I'd be on board,

26:13.320 --> 26:15.781
but that would be
so un-Victorian of me.

26:15.781 --> 26:18.326
The virtuous maiden
is supposed to be rescued

26:18.326 --> 26:21.621
by the dashing,
sometimes broody

26:21.621 --> 26:23.832
altogether charming hero.
- [laughs]

26:23.832 --> 26:27.210
And who is that? Is that--
is that meant to be you?

26:27.210 --> 26:28.545
<i>[laughter]</i>

26:28.545 --> 26:29.796
<i>- But that boat,
she can take it.</i>

26:29.796 --> 26:30.797
<i>You know.
</i>- No, no, I know,

26:30.797 --> 26:31.964
I know it well.

26:31.964 --> 26:33.215
I don't know
if Beck's told you,

26:33.215 --> 26:34.217
but I captained
the Nantucket Ferry

26:34.217 --> 26:35.468
for 16 years.

26:35.468 --> 26:36.552
- I did not know--
see, now,

26:36.552 --> 26:37.929
I feel like I've been telling

26:37.929 --> 26:39.471
Mickey Mantle
how to hold a bat.

26:39.471 --> 26:40.515
- Oh, please.

26:40.515 --> 26:41.974
- Do you sail, too?

26:41.974 --> 26:43.559
- Oh, God, no.
Never had the patience for it.

26:43.559 --> 26:45.854
- Oh, Dad, you know your way
around a sailboat.

26:45.854 --> 26:47.480
- Well, enough to know
that I'm all thumbs.

26:47.480 --> 26:49.065
Yeah, I've been out
a couple times.

26:49.065 --> 26:51.608
- You don't remember
the renters next door?

26:51.608 --> 26:53.653
They had that Sunfish
they let you take out.

26:53.653 --> 26:57.365
The Murphys. Their cars were
always blocking the driveway.

26:57.365 --> 26:59.826
- How's life in
the big city, dear?

26:59.826 --> 27:02.369
- It's great.
Thanks for asking.

27:02.369 --> 27:05.039
Oh, and we broke our
centerboard that one time.

27:05.039 --> 27:07.334
And--and the current took us,
like, halfway to Long Island.

27:07.334 --> 27:09.501
- Eh--what'd I say?
Not much of a sailor.

27:09.501 --> 27:11.837
- [laughs] But you do,
you remember it, right?

27:11.837 --> 27:13.548
I mean, it was pouring.

27:13.548 --> 27:16.343
I learned every swear word
in the book that day.

27:18.595 --> 27:20.596
- I don't think he remembers,
dear.

27:20.596 --> 27:23.682
- I think he can
speak for himself, Nancy.

27:23.682 --> 27:26.394
God, you know, you don't--
you don't have to protect him.

27:26.394 --> 27:28.438
Okay, he's--he's not a child.

27:28.438 --> 27:30.606
[silverware clanks]
- You're one to talk.

27:30.606 --> 27:32.692
- Excuse me?
- You invest nothing

27:32.692 --> 27:34.277
in this family.

27:34.277 --> 27:35.944
Nothing.

27:35.944 --> 27:37.572
Not even a call
to your father on his birthday.

27:37.572 --> 27:39.031
- You know what? Stop.

27:39.031 --> 27:40.532
You have no idea
what you're talking about.

27:40.532 --> 27:42.951
- 'Cause your father--
he's just an ATM to you.

27:42.951 --> 27:45.204
Right, Beck?
- Uh, please,

27:45.204 --> 27:46.789
let's not do this.
- Okay, I'm sorry.

27:46.789 --> 27:48.375
And what is he to you?

27:48.375 --> 27:50.501
A feature for your blog
so you can brag

27:50.501 --> 27:52.921
how you lifted him
out of the pits of despair?

27:52.921 --> 27:55.339
News flash!
He was sober when you met him.

27:55.339 --> 27:56.965
I was in the pits with him.

27:56.965 --> 27:59.719
And not because
I wasn't Christian enough.

27:59.719 --> 28:02.221
You didn't save him.

28:02.221 --> 28:03.515
You think he'll fall over

28:03.515 --> 28:05.099
if you pull your hand
out of his ass?

28:05.099 --> 28:08.103
- Guinevere! Enough.
- [sighs]

28:08.103 --> 28:09.269
- What the hell
are you looking at?

28:09.269 --> 28:10.313
- Guinevere.
- Do not talk

28:10.313 --> 28:11.564
to my daughter that way.

28:11.564 --> 28:13.857
- Okay, whatever.
I'm done.

28:13.857 --> 28:15.567
Oh, and, um...

28:15.567 --> 28:17.778
congrats on the baby.

28:17.778 --> 28:19.571
How blessed you all are.

28:19.571 --> 28:21.407
[slams table]

28:21.407 --> 28:24.411
<i>[dark tone]</i>

28:24.411 --> 28:27.663
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:47.433 --> 28:49.935
- Do you want him dead?

28:52.939 --> 28:54.941
- What?

28:58.278 --> 29:02.115
- Kinda feels like
you and he...

29:02.115 --> 29:03.825
have some unresolved stuff.

29:03.825 --> 29:07.537
Believe me, I'm king
of unresolved family issues.

29:07.537 --> 29:11.124
I know what people splitting
feels like.

29:11.124 --> 29:12.459
[sighs]

29:12.459 --> 29:15.878
I just wonder if, uh--

29:15.878 --> 29:18.423
Look, he's here.
He's alive.

29:18.423 --> 29:22.218
Use that as an opportunity
to talk to him.

29:24.386 --> 29:28.141
Or, uh, you're a writer.

29:28.141 --> 29:29.558
Could be helpful
to write about him.

29:29.558 --> 29:32.519
Cathartic, too.
- What are you doing?

29:32.519 --> 29:33.688
- N-nothing--I don't--

29:33.688 --> 29:35.064
- Do you hear yourself
right now?

29:35.064 --> 29:36.316
I mean, who the hell are you

29:36.316 --> 29:38.817
to tell me that
I have daddy issues.

29:38.817 --> 29:40.194
You don't even know me.

29:40.194 --> 29:41.195
- Hey, Beck, hang--
hang--hang on--

29:41.195 --> 29:43.155
- Just go.

29:43.155 --> 29:46.284
Leave me alone.
I'm serious.

29:49.621 --> 29:50.954
[sighs]

29:50.954 --> 29:57.961
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:07.888 --> 30:10.933
- Hey, hon.

30:10.933 --> 30:12.977
We're gonna get going.

30:15.563 --> 30:18.607
- Cool, um--

30:18.607 --> 30:22.569
Thanks for dinner.

30:22.569 --> 30:24.614
- This should cover the room.

30:39.461 --> 30:42.507
- It's hard for me
to see you with them.

30:42.507 --> 30:45.759
I keep waiting
for you to be you again.

30:45.759 --> 30:47.679
- Well, this is me, Guinevere.

30:47.679 --> 30:49.638
- No, it's not. You were--

30:49.638 --> 30:50.890
- Reckless.

30:50.890 --> 30:52.224
And out of control.

30:52.224 --> 30:54.894
And, honey,
you were a kid, you--

30:54.894 --> 30:56.479
You didn't see
what was going on.

30:56.479 --> 30:58.439
- Yes--

30:58.439 --> 31:00.441
yes, I did.

31:00.441 --> 31:03.403
And you were more
than just an addict.

31:04.903 --> 31:07.240
I miss you.

31:10.826 --> 31:14.580
[sighs] Whatever.

31:14.580 --> 31:16.874
You know, I tell people
that you're dead.

31:18.750 --> 31:22.755
Kinda feels like you did die
that day in the basement.

31:22.755 --> 31:25.758
<i>[somber music]</i>

31:25.758 --> 31:27.009
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:27.009 --> 31:29.429
- I'm sorry you feel that way.

31:31.806 --> 31:33.766
- You were a good sailor.

31:41.148 --> 31:44.152
- Well, maybe you can
tell me about it sometime.

31:44.152 --> 31:47.029
Maybe in Vermont.

31:47.029 --> 31:49.240
Over Christmas.

31:52.326 --> 31:54.453
- Like I said,
I'll have to let you know.

31:57.123 --> 32:04.130
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:11.136 --> 32:14.140
<i>[somber pop music]</i>

32:14.140 --> 32:18.019
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:18.019 --> 32:19.854
[sighs]

32:19.854 --> 32:26.903
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:41.334 --> 32:42.876
[sighs]

32:42.876 --> 32:44.711
<i>On the plywood
over the bay window,</i>

32:44.711 --> 32:47.589
<i>we spray paint taunts
at Hurricane Isabel.</i>

32:47.589 --> 32:50.259
<i>Cow her into a tropical storm.</i>

32:50.259 --> 32:54.012
<i>Her moon tide, though,
carries your beach chair away.</i>

32:58.643 --> 33:01.019
<i>Sea glass and Springsteen.</i>

33:01.019 --> 33:04.565
<i>The beached whale,
the silent walk home.</i>

33:04.565 --> 33:07.693
<i>The grill that doesn't start
on the Fourth of July.</i>

33:11.029 --> 33:13.782
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:13.782 --> 33:18.078
<i>The woman at the drug store
you hit on who isn't Mom.</i>

33:18.078 --> 33:21.124
<i>The renters
blocking the drive.</i>

33:21.124 --> 33:24.669
<i>The string of my sweatshirt
I gnaw on.</i>

33:25.920 --> 33:28.881
<i>Morning sun over Wauwinet.</i>

33:28.881 --> 33:31.467
<i>The red ladle over the pan.</i>

33:31.467 --> 33:34.136
<i>Your wrist, the perfect cant.</i>

33:34.136 --> 33:36.138
[phone buzzes]

33:37.807 --> 33:41.644
<i>You leave for the 8:20 to
Hyannis with one commandment.</i>

33:41.644 --> 33:44.689
<i>Get the batter off the ladle
while it's wet.</i>

33:46.065 --> 33:48.067
[sighs]

33:52.904 --> 33:54.906
<i>The ladle's left in the sink.</i>

33:57.076 --> 33:58.952
<i>Mom lets it soak.</i>

33:58.952 --> 34:01.079
<i>Leave it, she says.</i>

34:01.079 --> 34:04.416
<i>You go away,
and we come home.</i>

34:04.416 --> 34:07.252
<i>And what's left of you.
It loosens.</i>

34:07.252 --> 34:09.588
<i>And the water
carries it away.</i>

34:09.588 --> 34:16.596
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:20.391 --> 34:22.143
[water running]

34:22.143 --> 34:24.269
[phone buzzes]

34:25.855 --> 34:28.815
[phone buzzing]

34:28.815 --> 34:36.532
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:36.532 --> 34:38.742
[phone buzzes]

34:47.293 --> 34:49.295
[sighs]

34:53.257 --> 34:58.387
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:58.387 --> 35:00.472
[knocking]

35:00.472 --> 35:02.809
[inhales, exhales]

35:02.809 --> 35:05.018
[locks unlatching]

35:05.018 --> 35:10.817
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:10.817 --> 35:16.989
They say girls with daddy
issues are really good in bed.

35:16.989 --> 35:18.490
- Mm.

35:18.490 --> 35:24.496
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:24.496 --> 35:28.876
- I like who I am
with you, Joe.

35:28.876 --> 35:33.338
<i>- ♪ You can see it
in my eyes ♪</i>

35:33.338 --> 35:35.715
<i>♪ On the level ♪</i>

35:35.715 --> 35:38.719
<i>♪ Comin' out of nowhere ♪</i>

35:38.719 --> 35:43.224
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:43.224 --> 35:45.559
- Mm, mm--sorry I didn't call.

35:45.559 --> 35:47.519
Is it okay if I come in?

35:50.856 --> 35:53.943
<i>- ♪ I'm rebel ♪</i>

35:53.943 --> 35:58.239
<i>♪ Take a breath
and say a prayer ♪</i>

35:58.239 --> 35:59.865
- Ah! [laughs]

35:59.865 --> 36:03.327
<i>- ♪ You play your game,
I take my time ♪</i>

36:03.327 --> 36:04.829
- Ahh!

36:04.829 --> 36:08.123
<i>- ♪ You take your aim ♪</i>

36:08.123 --> 36:12.128
<i>♪ Commit your crime ♪</i>

36:12.128 --> 36:14.463
- Ahh!

36:14.463 --> 36:17.507
- Oh!
- [laughs] Ah!

36:17.507 --> 36:19.719
Too rough for you, Goldberg?

36:19.719 --> 36:20.969
- Not at all.

36:20.969 --> 36:23.222
<i>- ♪ I'm a rebel ♪</i>

36:23.222 --> 36:27.893
<i>♪ Comin' out of nowhere ♪</i>

36:27.893 --> 36:29.561
- Uh!
- Yeah!

36:29.561 --> 36:33.565
<i>- ♪ Take a breath
and say a prayer ♪</i>

36:33.565 --> 36:36.735
- [sighing]

36:39.112 --> 36:42.199
[sighs] I want you, Joe.

36:44.117 --> 36:47.204
<i>- ♪ Comin' out of no--rebel ♪</i>

36:47.204 --> 36:50.248
<i>♪ Comin' out of no--
rebel ♪</i>

36:50.248 --> 36:53.168
<i>♪ Comin' out of no-- ♪</i>

36:53.168 --> 36:56.338
<i>♪ Comin' out
of no-- ♪</i>

36:56.338 --> 36:57.757
[both moan]

37:01.092 --> 37:04.096
<i>[upbeat, light music]</i>

37:04.096 --> 37:06.349
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:06.349 --> 37:08.099
- [sighs]

37:08.099 --> 37:15.106
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:18.443 --> 37:19.945
- Hey, stranger.

37:19.945 --> 37:22.530
- Ohh.

37:22.530 --> 37:24.199
- You drool in your sleep.

37:24.199 --> 37:26.452
So cute.

37:26.452 --> 37:28.036
- Were you watching me?

37:28.036 --> 37:30.664
- Maybe.

37:30.664 --> 37:33.291
- Uh-oh. Stalker.

37:33.291 --> 37:35.628
- Learn from the best.

37:38.630 --> 37:41.634
<i>[sentimental music]</i>

37:41.634 --> 37:46.764
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:46.764 --> 37:49.891
[both laugh]

37:49.891 --> 37:52.936
- How--how did you
figure out where I live?

37:52.936 --> 37:54.313
- [sighs]

37:54.313 --> 37:57.108
The bearded guy
from the bookstore.

37:57.108 --> 37:59.068
- Oh.

38:02.655 --> 38:05.324
Mm, you taste like maple syrup.

38:10.496 --> 38:13.164
- Mm, wait.
- What?

38:13.164 --> 38:15.376
- [sighs]

38:17.293 --> 38:21.507
I have to apologize
about our talk.

38:21.507 --> 38:23.842
I was a hostile goose.

38:23.842 --> 38:25.260
- A hostile goose?

38:25.260 --> 38:27.512
- Yeah, geese are total dicks.

38:27.512 --> 38:29.264
But, uh, no, seriously.

38:29.264 --> 38:32.851
You called me on my shit,

38:32.851 --> 38:35.730
and I took it really poorly.

38:35.730 --> 38:38.356
Because, um--well, because

38:38.356 --> 38:40.025
you were totally right,
and I didn't wanna hear it

38:40.025 --> 38:41.527
and I'm sorry.

38:41.527 --> 38:43.320
- Like you said,
we barely know each other.

38:43.320 --> 38:44.947
And here I was, trying--
- You really don't think

38:44.947 --> 38:46.699
we know each other?

38:46.699 --> 38:49.326
I mean, I was just--I was angry
when I said that and--

38:49.326 --> 38:52.288
- Look...

38:52.288 --> 38:56.876
sometimes I could swear
I've known you forever.

38:56.876 --> 38:58.501
But in the grand scheme
of things,

38:58.501 --> 39:00.336
Not long enough

39:00.336 --> 39:01.630
for me to be commenting

39:01.630 --> 39:03.173
on your relationship
with your father.

39:03.173 --> 39:04.632
- Oh, you were just trying
to help me see

39:04.632 --> 39:07.135
that I'm full of shit.
[laughs]

39:07.135 --> 39:09.387
And you were sweet.

39:09.387 --> 39:13.266
Uh, it's funny. I feel like
every guy I date is--

39:13.266 --> 39:15.561
they're either messes--
like my dad was--

39:15.561 --> 39:17.228
or they're like my dad is now,

39:17.228 --> 39:21.692
trying to be something
that they think they should.

39:21.692 --> 39:23.152
Or they're me.

39:23.152 --> 39:25.070
Both a mess and a fraud.

39:25.070 --> 39:26.572
- You're not a fraud.

39:26.572 --> 39:29.574
- So just a mess?
- No, not more than anyone.

39:29.574 --> 39:32.786
- But then there is you.

39:32.786 --> 39:35.246
I mean, you're not trying to be
anything than what you are.

39:35.246 --> 39:37.833
You're just you.
There's not an ounce

39:37.833 --> 39:39.376
of falseness in you.

39:39.376 --> 39:42.922
I mean, you drink Cafe Bustelo
and you own starch.

39:42.922 --> 39:45.507
And I like how you don't care
about dumb shit

39:45.507 --> 39:47.510
like posting your life online.

39:47.510 --> 39:49.929
I mean, it's--
it's a revelation.

39:51.847 --> 39:55.851
Do you know how many selfies
I've taken on the toilet?

39:55.851 --> 39:57.018
A lot.

39:57.018 --> 39:59.021
[laughs]

40:01.898 --> 40:04.402
Okay, instead of sitting here,

40:04.402 --> 40:05.443
watching you judge me,

40:05.443 --> 40:07.028
I'm gonna go pee.
- No.

40:07.028 --> 40:08.364
I'm not--

40:08.364 --> 40:11.157
- And try not to take
a selfie.

40:12.827 --> 40:14.119
[door closes]

40:14.119 --> 40:15.454
<i>- What are the chances</i>

40:15.454 --> 40:17.081
<i>I'm getting a follow-up
review?</i>

40:17.081 --> 40:21.293
<i>[upbeat pop music]</i>

40:21.293 --> 40:24.295
<i>- ♪ Heaven ♪</i>

40:24.295 --> 40:29.092
<i>♪ I'm in heaven ♪</i>

40:29.092 --> 40:33.556
<i>- Apparently
I've redeemed myself.</i>

40:33.556 --> 40:34.974
<i>Far be it for me to stop you</i>

40:34.974 --> 40:37.809
<i>from shouting it
from the rooftops.</i>

40:37.809 --> 40:43.148
<i>Plus, I guess it is nice
to hear it from your friends.</i>

40:43.148 --> 40:45.067
<i>Even if not all of them</i>

40:45.067 --> 40:46.943
<i>can share in your happiness.</i>

40:46.943 --> 40:50.489
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:50.489 --> 40:52.324
<i>It's really too bad</i>

40:52.324 --> 40:53.826
<i>the one whose approval
you crave most</i>

40:53.826 --> 40:55.452
<i>isn't my biggest fan.</i>

40:55.452 --> 41:02.501
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:04.961 --> 41:10.634
<i>Fortunately, Paco's a
remarkably quick reader.</i>

41:10.634 --> 41:12.677
<i>I can return the book I,
of course,</i>

41:12.677 --> 41:15.639
<i>never had any intention
of keeping.</i>

41:15.639 --> 41:18.099
<i>And if that's not enough,</i>

41:18.099 --> 41:22.103
<i>if Peach still
has a problem...</i>

41:22.103 --> 41:24.023
<i>well, every relationship has</i>

41:24.023 --> 41:27.108
<i>its obstacles to
overcome, right?</i>

41:27.108 --> 41:29.862
<i>I won't let her get
in the way of us, Beck.</i>

41:29.862 --> 41:31.155
<i>I won't.</i>

41:31.155 --> 41:33.865
<i>- ♪ I'm in heaven ♪</i>
